APA Insurance has bagged 11 awards out of 18 categories in the Annual Insurance Awards. The third largest insurance company by market share scooped five overall winners’ positions in claim settlement for life business, fraud detection and protection, major loss, training award and best in customer satisfaction index in its general underwriting business. “This is an enormous recognition by the industry and every member of APA Apollo is humbled,” Apollo Group CEO Ashok Shah said in a statement. “These awards reaffirm the successful implementation of our customer centric strategies over the years. It is a great boost which will act as a further incentive for our winning team.” Product innovation, effective use of Information Communication Technology  and a customer oriented approach are some of the criteria judges looked at to award winners.